    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Yellow wood with dark stripes obtained from the species Lavoa klaineana, native to Africa. Tigerwood has a naturally glossy surface with a fine uniform texture. It is used for furniture, veneer, gunstocks, inlay, billiard tables, and cabinets.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
